13/03/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Defence Ministry said Wednesday (12 March) that 15 members of a chemical, biological and nuclear decontamination unit have left for the Persian Gulf. Another 55 decontamination specialists are to join them next week as part of Romania's pledge to help in any operation to disarm Saddam Hussein's regime. About 4,000 US troops have already set up base in the Romanian port city of Constanta. (AP - 12/03/03)
